Compilation:

	make

	To clean up the generated executable and object files, run:

	make clean

How to Run

Pass a single text file containing the regex definitions and expression as a command-line argument:

./parse test.txt

Project Files

    lexer.l: The Flex file that tokenizes the input string and handles escaped Unicode characters.

    parser.y: The Bison file that defines the grammar rules, resolves operator precedence, and builds the AST.

    tree.c / tree.h: The C logic and structs for dynamically allocating, printing, and safely freeing the AST nodes.

    Makefile: Automates the compilation process.
